AS OF NOVEMBER 26, 2002, THE AGGREGATE

MARKET VALUE OF COMMON STOCK HELD BY NON-AFFILIATES (BASED ON

THE CLOSING PRICE ON SUCH DATE AS REPORTED ON THE NEW YORK STOCK

EXCHANGE-COMPOSITE TRANSACTIONS) WAS $38.8 BILLION. ALL

EXECUTIVE OFFICERS AND DIRECTORS OF THE REGISTRANT AND ALL

PERSONS FILING A SCHEDULE 13D WITH THE SECURITIES AND

EXCHANGE COMMISSION IN RESPECT TO REGISTRANTS COMMON STOCK

HAVE BEEN DEEMED, SOLELY FOR THE PURPOSE OF THE FOREGOING

CALCULATION, TO BE AFFILIATES OF THE REGISTRANT.

THERE WERE 2,042,158,130 SHARES OF COMMON

STOCK OUTSTANDING AS OF NOVEMBER 26, 2002.

