ITEM 5.

MARKET FOR THE COMPANYS COMMON STOCK AND

RELATED STOCKHOLDER MATTERS

THE COMPANYS COMMON STOCK IS LISTED ON THE

NEW YORK AND PACIFIC STOCK EXCHANGES UNDER THE TICKER

SYMBOL DIS.

ON MARCH 20, 2001, THE COMPANY CONVERTED ALL

OF ITS OUTSTANDING INTERNET GROUP COMMON STOCK (NYSE

SYMBOL DIG) INTO DISNEY COMMON STOCK. EACH OUTSTANDING

SHARE OF INTERNET GROUP COMMON STOCK WAS CONVERTED INTO 0.19353

OF A SHARE OF DISNEY COMMON STOCK, RESULTING IN THE ISSUANCE OF

APPROXIMATELY 8.6 MILLION SHARES OF DISNEY COMMON STOCK.

