STOCK OPTION ACCOUNTING

THE COMPANY HAS ELECTED TO CONTINUE USING THE

INTRINSIC-VALUE METHOD OF ACCOUNTING FOR STOCK-BASED AWARDS

GRANTED TO EMPLOYEES UNTIL A UNIFORM METHOD OF VALUING AND

EXPENSING STOCK OPTIONS IS PROMULGATED. ACCORDINGLY, THE COMPANY

HAS NOT RECOGNIZED COMPENSATION EXPENSE FOR THE FAIR VALUE OF

ITS STOCK-BASED AWARDS TO EMPLOYEES IN ITS CONSOLIDATED

STATEMENTS OF INCOME. COMPANIES ELECTING TO REMAIN WITH THE

INTRINSIC-VALUE METHOD ACCOUNTING IN APB 25 MUST MAKE PRO

FORMA DISCLOSURES, AS IF THE FAIR VALUE BASED METHOD OF

ACCOUNTING HAD BEEN APPLIED.

