16

SUBSEQUENT EVENT

ON NOVEMBER 27, 2002, THE COMPANY RELEASED ITS

NEW ANIMATED FILM,

TREASURE PLANET.

THE FILMS

OPENING WEEK BOX OFFICE PERFORMANCE WAS SIGNIFICANTLY LESS THAN

EXPECTATIONS, REQUIRING A DOWNWARD REVISION OF ITS PROJECTED

REVENUES AND A CORRESPONDING $74 MILLION WRITEDOWN OF

CAPITALIZED FILM PRODUCTION COSTS. IN ACCORDANCE WITH FILM

ACCOUNTING RULES, THIS REDUCTION OF CAPITALIZED FILM PRODUCTION

COSTS WAS RECORDED AS OF SEPTEMBER 30, 2002. AS A RESULT,

THE COMPANYS FISCAL 2002 EARNINGS DIFFER FROM THE AMOUNTS

INITIALLY REPORTED IN ITS NOVEMBER 7, 2002 EARNINGS RELEASE

TO REFLECT THIS CHANGE IN ESTIMATE.

